definition: the percentage of a sum of money charged for its use

positive_examples: This is an example of interest rate.
The interest rate demonstrated clear characteristics.
We observed interest rate in this context.
A typical case of interest rate would involve these features.
The concept of interest rate applies here.
The percentage charged by lenders to borrowers for the use of money, typically expressed as an annual percentage.
negative_examples: This is an example of inflation, not interest rate.
This represents economic indicator in general.
The document was filed in the cabinet.
She walked to the store to buy groceries.
training_hints.disambiguation: Not to be confused with: Inflation, or other types of EconomicIndicator
